commit.message: Correct contributor name for ConduitVsPipes example

README: Use GitHub-Flavored Markdown, not HTML, for hyperlinks

Fixes #279.

Criterion.Analysis: Fix -Wx-partial warning

This was uncovered by GHC 9.8, where -Wx-partial is included in -Wall.

Require optparse-applicative-0.18.* as the minimum

Also add explicit dependencies on `prettyprinter` and
`prettyprinter-ansi-terminal`. With this change, we have expunged any traces of
`ansi-wl-pprint` from `criterion`.

Support building with optparse-applicative-0.18.*

This adds the necessary CPP to support building `criterion` with
`optparse-applicative-0.18.*` as well as older versions of the library. In a
future, major release of `criterion`, we will require
`optparse-applicative-0.18.*` as the minimum and explicitly depend on
`prettyprinter`.

Specialize benchmarking loops aggressively

This mirrors similar changes applied to `tasty-bench` in
https://github.com/Bodigrim/tasty-bench/commit/9c8699014b9ab449e442c15a9ef11473a730a831.

Fixes #270.

Remove mentions of cabal v1-install (#268)

* Remove mentions of cabal v1-install

* Suggest cabal run script for getting started example
* Sync Fibber.hs from examples to tutorial
* Re-run Fibber.hs to produce fibber.html
* Remove mention of cabal v1-install in README

Closes #267

* Update index.md too

commit.message:
Remove entries from www/ directory from the linguist statistics

This should update the project's language bar and tag it as a Haskell
project.

Make nf' and whnf' robust against eta-expansion changes

As seen in ghc#21948 (https://gitlab.haskell.org/ghc/ghc/-/issues/21948), whether
or not `go` gets eta-expanded crucially determines whether `nf'` is a
function which computes an `IO ()` action or a function which computes a
result of type `(# RealWorld State#, () #)`.

In the former case, the call to `seq` in `runBenchmark` will force the
computation of the `IO ()` action, which can be computed without
dependency on the State# token, and therefore before any IO takes place. This
defeats the point of the function which is supposed to run the loop
inside the IO action (so that measure can correct measure the runtime
stats).

The fix is to make both branches of the loop depend on the state token so
that the loop can't be evaluated before the whole IO action is executed.

Fix #168 (again) by factoring out common sub-Parsers

I thought I had fixed #168 in 45c135d67980c3690c3ad8f01c45667f2beab33c, but I
had overlooked that the `Parser` for `--match` appears on both sides of a
`(<|>)` expression, thereby duplicating its `--help` text. A somewhat
heavy-handed but serviceable solution is to pair up the common sub-`Parsers`
between the `Run` and `RunIters` `Mode`s as much as possible, which prevents
the `--match` `Parser` from ever being run more than once. I've left a lengthy
comment explaining how this works.
Add peak bytes allocated field to Measured

commit.message:
Tweak aeson version bounds in criterion.cabal

We've been bitten by a lack of upper version bounds on `aeson` (see #246),
so let's add some upper version bounds. Also, remove some extraneous version
bounds on `aeson` in a test suite that are implied by the version bounds in
the library component.
